WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.730 --> 00:00:07.420
Inarizaki High School is 
switching out players.

2
00:00:08.410 --> 00:00:10.880
Taking the place of #4 Ojiro Aran,

3
00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:13.940
is the captain, #1 Kita Shinsuke.

4
00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:19.230
He's a player we didn't 
get to see in the videos.

5
00:00:19.230 --> 00:00:19.990
Yeah.

6
00:00:20.530 --> 00:00:23.590
I wanted to put a little more
 pressure on Ojiro, but...

7
00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:28.550
Listen, guys. You don't 
have to be that guarded.

8
00:00:29.640 --> 00:00:33.550
I'm just a substitute. 
I'm here to tide them over.

9
00:00:35.300 --> 00:00:37.050
So you don't need to be scared of me.

10
00:00:51.030 --> 00:00:58.030
Haikyu

11
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:13.400
Episode 20: Leader

12
00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:15.150
Someone's always watching, Shin-chan.

13
00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:20.110
The gods are everywhere.

14
00:02:20.740 --> 00:02:22.920
So someone's always watching.

15
00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:24.310
Gin!

16
00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:28.210
Why'd you force that spike earlier?

17
00:02:28.630 --> 00:02:33.540
I-It felt like the game was going in 
Karasuno's favor, so I tried to stop it.

18
00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.380
And that's supposed to happen 
by you getting blocked?

19
00:02:41.370 --> 00:02:45.800
Everyone's so on edge as soon 
as Shinsuke enters the court.

20
00:02:47.110 --> 00:02:49.940
Well, his sound arguments are 
like a punch to the gut.

21
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:54.110
Nice serve!

22
00:02:58.810 --> 00:02:59.820
Right between...

23
00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:01.280
Got it!

24
00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:02.270
Daichi-san!

25
00:03:02.270 --> 00:03:04.700
Looks like he tried to get them 
to set from the back lines.

26
00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:03.740
Sorry, it's short!

27
00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:04.700
Azumane-san!

28
00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:08.810
Yes!

29
00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:15.450
Akagi!

30
00:03:17.210 --> 00:03:19.170
Free ball!

31
00:03:23.330 --> 00:03:24.680
I hate this.

32
00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:32.480
Gin!

33
00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:35.980
Hell yeah!

34
00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:37.940
We Don't Need the Memories

35
00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:40.330
Inarizaki's break point! That one 
point is gonna hurt Karasuno!

36
00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:40.900
Inarizaki                                                          Karasuno

37
00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:44.110
Nice kill, Hitoshi! Jump, 
jump, Hitoshi! One more time!

38
00:03:41.590 --> 00:03:44.110
I have a bad feeling about this.

39
00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:47.450
They got the break point,

40
00:03:47.450 --> 00:03:50.440
but now, it somehow feels like plays 
the boys could've made earlier

41
00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:52.020
suddenly aren't possible.

42
00:03:53.270 --> 00:03:56.340
Guys like Shinsuke show up
 every once in a while.

43
00:03:56.930 --> 00:04:00.420
They're definitely not the star, but their 
presence takes over the whole court.

44
00:04:01.160 --> 00:04:04.920
He's had that kind of presence 
ever since middle school.

45
00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:08.180
Their #4 won't hit a straight shot.

46
00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:10.040
Right!

47
00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:13.890
He never did anything unnecessary 
and his words were precise.

48
00:04:13.890 --> 00:04:16.310
His plays needed a bit of work,
 but they were thorough.

49
00:04:17.010 --> 00:04:18.860
And now...

50
00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:22.130
Shinsuke is overflowing with confidence.

51
00:04:22.130 --> 00:04:25.820
Not confidence that says that 
he's stronger than others.

52
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:29.420
But confidence that ensures 
that he won't mess up.

53
00:04:30.290 --> 00:04:34.380
How does Kita-san just pop onto the 
court and play flawlessly like that?

54
00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:36.830
He's got way more EXP than you.

55
00:04:36.830 --> 00:04:42.830
But apparently, Kita-san never played 
in a game until his third year.

56
00:04:42.830 --> 00:04:44.570
Huh? Seriously?

57
00:04:44.570 --> 00:04:47.440
But he totally acts like 
he's a seasoned veteran.

58
00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:49.630
Which means even if
 he played in middle school,

59
00:04:49.630 --> 00:04:52.860
he didn't have much of a chance 
to play in high school.

60
00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:56.400
Actually, not only was he not on the 
starting lineup in middle school,

61
00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:58.920
they never even gave him a uniform.

62
00:04:58.920 --> 00:04:59.610
What?

63
00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:04.950
I don't understand why
 anyone ever gets nervous.

64
00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:06.660
What?

65
00:05:06.660 --> 00:05:09.620
What are you, some kind of robot?

66
00:05:09.620 --> 00:05:11.800
I mean, I've been on to you, but...

67
00:05:12.320 --> 00:05:16.870
You only get nervous because you try to be 
more powerful than you usually are, right?

68
00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:20.890
I mean, when you do day-to-day 
things like eat or use the toilet,

69
00:05:20.890 --> 00:05:23.590
you don't get nervous.

70
00:05:24.370 --> 00:05:25.880
That should apply to volleyball, too.

71
00:05:27.190 --> 00:05:30.780
If it's something you can do during practice,
 there's no reason to get nervous.

72
00:05:33.390 --> 00:05:35.310
Inarizaki                                                           Karasuno

73
00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:39.020
Get out there!

74
00:05:39.390 --> 00:05:42.830
Oh, there he is. 
Karasuno's first-year relief server.

75
00:05:42.830 --> 00:05:44.740
He seems pretty good at scoring.

76
00:05:47.450 --> 00:05:48.910
That felt good!

77
00:05:58.200 --> 00:06:01.590
Shinsuke's abilities could be 
considered better than average.

78
00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:05.510
It's not like he's physically or 
technically impressive, or stands out.

79
00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:07.000
But...

80
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:10.970
Anything he can do during practices, 
he can also absolutely pull off in matches.

81
00:06:11.460 --> 00:06:16.380
The best praise you could give 
Shinsuke is to not be surprised.

82
00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:23.660
What, Atsumu? Did you catch a cold?

83
00:06:23.660 --> 00:06:25.100
Shouldn't you be resting?

84
00:06:25.100 --> 00:06:28.070
This is nothing! I'll get worse 
if I don't play volleyball!

85
00:06:29.330 --> 00:06:32.340
That's the spirit! 
Love of volleyball conquers all!

86
00:06:32.340 --> 00:06:33.320
Go home.

87
00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:40.370
Don't compliment him when he's 
obviously not taking care of himself.

88
00:06:41.430 --> 00:06:43.210
Why am I in trouble?

89
00:06:43.210 --> 00:06:44.280
Ice cold.

90
00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:46.000
Now I'm gonna catch a cold.

91
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:47.970
Boys' Volleyball Team

92
00:06:46.380 --> 00:06:47.970
What... the hell?!

93
00:06:49.030 --> 00:06:51.670
Couldn't he be nicer about it?!

94
00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:56.100
Atsumu,
Make sure you
 eat and sleep
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hKita

95
00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:56.100
Pickled Plums

96
00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:56.100
Warm
Lemon

97
00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:02.770
You're gonna make me cry!

98
00:07:02.770 --> 00:07:04.580
Pickled plums?!

99
00:07:05.190 --> 00:07:08.490
You gotta do it every day. 
Properly, every day.

100
00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:11.990
Taking care of yourself.

101
00:07:13.490 --> 00:07:15.620
Cleaning, tidying up...

102
00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:17.340
Thank you for the food.

103
00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:18.950
Your greetings.

104
00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:21.670
Volleyball.

105
00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:28.780
Don't worry about it.

106
00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:32.660
That's Shinsuke's ritual.

107
00:07:33.630 --> 00:07:37.930
The gods are everywhere.

108
00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:43.150
That's what Grandma would always tell me,

109
00:07:43.150 --> 00:07:46.940
but at some point, I stopped caring.

110
00:07:48.130 --> 00:07:50.890
It's not like I'm doing this for the gods.

111
00:07:52.380 --> 00:07:56.910
Repetition, being methodical, 
and being thorough just feels nice.

112
00:07:58.530 --> 00:08:00.920
Someone's always watching.

113
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.960
#1, Kita!

114
00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:05.580
Yes, sir.

115
00:08:07.290 --> 00:08:10.510
Inarizaki High School

116
00:08:14.440 --> 00:08:16.950
Next up, #2, Omimi!

117
00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:17.470
Yes, sir.

118
00:08:24.940 --> 00:08:29.550
I figured Kita-san was basically a robot.

119
00:08:29.550 --> 00:08:30.600
Yeah...

120
00:08:35.590 --> 00:08:39.820
When an adult says, "The process 
matters more than the results,"

121
00:08:39.820 --> 00:08:41.720
kids aren't really gonna understand.

122
00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:44.920
Results are everything!

123
00:08:45.280 --> 00:08:48.230
But I totally agree with the adults.

124
00:08:49.800 --> 00:08:53.480
I'm basically built from my daily routine,

125
00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:55.560
and the results are nothing 
more than byproduct.

126
00:08:56.640 --> 00:09:00.650
It's not like I'm gonna make 
a living playing volleyball.

127
00:09:01.470 --> 00:09:06.440
Inarizaki High School

128
00:09:02.710 --> 00:09:06.440
But... I wonder if this is a result, too...

129
00:09:10.880 --> 00:09:12.760
Who cares about the small stuff?!

130
00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:16.600
You don't need a reason for emotions! 
If you're happy, you're happy!

131
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:23.660
What're you laughing for?!

132
00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:26.120
Yeah...

133
00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:32.540
I don't need any applause.

134
00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:35.060
I'm just going to do what I need to do.

135
00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:42.680
If Aran, Rintaro, or Atsumu throw 
our enemies into despair...

136
00:09:46.100 --> 00:09:50.650
Shinsuke's role is to prolong that despair.

137
00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:53.610
Nice kill, Hitoshi! Push it, push it,
 Hitoshi! One more time!

138
00:09:50.650 --> 00:09:53.610
Inarizaki                                                                                                Karasuno

139
00:09:50.990 --> 00:09:53.610
And Inarizaki High is at set point!

140
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:57.820
Don't give up! You're only 8 points behind!

141
00:09:57.820 --> 00:10:00.450
They're probably going 
to lose this set.

142
00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:02.390
But what's important is how they do that.

143
00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:05.230
The final set is going to be affected

144
00:10:04.290 --> 00:10:06.990
Concentrate! Let's break their streak!

145
00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:07.140
by however the end of the 
second set plays out.

146
00:10:06.990 --> 00:10:08.200
Right!

147
00:10:07.720 --> 00:10:10.000
Please end on a positive note!

148
00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:10.000
Cut it off on the one!

149
00:10:11.030 --> 00:10:14.060
Good, good. Looks like we've got this set.

150
00:10:14.060 --> 00:10:15.850
But you never know.

151
00:10:15.850 --> 00:10:19.400
Last year, the tables turned on us 
even though we were six points ahead.

152
00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:21.070
They could go for a new record.

153
00:10:21.070 --> 00:10:21.970
What?!

154
00:10:22.360 --> 00:10:25.830
The first- and second-years
 are always moody.

155
00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:31.770
Seriously...

156
00:10:31.770 --> 00:10:34.110
It's not like he ever yells or hits anyone,

157
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:36.320
but the pressure he puts on 
everyone else is so intense.

158
00:10:36.320 --> 00:10:39.270
It doesn't matter what it is. 
This guy just never gives.

159
00:10:40.130 --> 00:10:41.500
Damn it, he's already here.

160
00:10:41.110 --> 00:10:42.370
Morning Practice

161
00:10:41.110 --> 00:10:42.370
He's Always First

162
00:10:42.760 --> 00:10:44.490
I wonder if there's a shortcut somewhere...

163
00:10:44.490 --> 00:10:46.620
Morning
 Practice

164
00:10:44.490 --> 00:10:46.620
Of Course He Goes All-Out

165
00:10:46.620 --> 00:10:49.000
What's a failing grade?

166
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:54.670
Academics

167
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:54.670
His Grades Are Always at the Top of His Class

168
00:10:51.840 --> 00:10:55.180
I seriously wish I could catch 
him with his guard down.

169
00:10:55.180 --> 00:10:57.240
I know. For example...

170
00:10:57.640 --> 00:11:01.900
Catching him using baby talk with a pet.

171
00:11:01.900 --> 00:11:03.510
That's a good wittle boy!

172
00:11:01.930 --> 00:11:03.510
* Imagined

173
00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:07.740
I don't put Kita in just 
to strengthen our defense.

174
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:10.000
Whenever there's a difference in the scores,

175
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.200
the second-years either panic 
or let their guard down.

176
00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:16.270
They should have authority, 
but they're mentally weak.

177
00:11:16.270 --> 00:11:19.860
Inarizaki High School

178
00:11:16.870 --> 00:11:19.860
Kita's the only one who 
can whip them into shape.

179
00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:26.310
Atsumu is aggressive and hates losing, 
which can be a disadvantage at times.

180
00:11:27.090 --> 00:11:29.470
Despite the fact that Osamu 
seems calmer than Atsumu,

181
00:11:29.470 --> 00:11:30.870
they still share the same DNA.

182
00:11:31.890 --> 00:11:35.180
Gin feels responsible and is passionate, 
which causes him to rush.

183
00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:40.040
When we're ahead or it looks like 
we're going to win, Suna starts slacking.

184
00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:41.430
I'm watching all of you.

185
00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:46.930
Their #5 turned this around 
at the end of the first set.

186
00:11:46.930 --> 00:11:49.270
We Don't Need the Memories

187
00:11:46.930 --> 00:11:49.270
Nice serve!

188
00:11:47.390 --> 00:11:49.920
In that case, I'll use my serves...

189
00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:51.430
to drag him back down!

190
00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:54.280
Ryu!

191
00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:56.150
They're not holding back despite their lead!

192
00:11:56.150 --> 00:11:57.110
Yes!

193
00:11:58.110 --> 00:11:59.530
Free ball!

194
00:12:01.890 --> 00:12:03.150
Here it comes!

195
00:12:03.150 --> 00:12:04.610
Just try and stop me!

196
00:12:15.130 --> 00:12:18.590
We Don't Need the Memories

197
00:12:18.590 --> 00:12:23.660
Nice kill, Rintaro! Jump, 
jump, Rintaro! One more time!

198
00:12:24.630 --> 00:12:27.220
Inarizaki                                                           Karasuno

199
00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:28.220
A powerful serve followed 
by a powerful quick

200
00:12:28.220 --> 00:12:32.570
allows Inarizaki High School to 
instantly take the second set!

201
00:12:32.570 --> 00:12:35.980
Karasuno High School is at a loss!

202
00:12:35.980 --> 00:12:42.990
Haikyu!!

203
00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:49.990
Haikyu!!

204
00:12:49.990 --> 00:12:54.410
We Don't Need the Memories

205
00:12:51.730 --> 00:12:54.410
The quicks from Inarizaki's #10 
just keep coming!

206
00:12:54.410 --> 00:12:56.200
Not to mention, Karasuno's blockers seem

207
00:12:56.200 --> 00:12:58.670
like they're on top of things, 
but their defense is full of holes.

208
00:12:58.670 --> 00:13:00.800
They keep getting around the same guy.

209
00:13:01.780 --> 00:13:04.510
Come after me already.

210
00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:06.860
All right! Let's change things up!

211
00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:07.590
Right!

212
00:13:11.090 --> 00:13:14.430
I've never seen Nishinoya-kun 
be quiet off the court.

213
00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:18.620
I want to believe it's because 
he's concentrating, but...

214
00:13:21.170 --> 00:13:24.040
You're doing that thing you do
 when you mess up practice,

215
00:13:24.040 --> 00:13:24.820
Nishinoya.

216
00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:32.390
Get a grip! You practiced more than enough!

217
00:13:33.390 --> 00:13:35.190
You'll be fine.

218
00:13:35.510 --> 00:13:36.950
Yeah.

219
00:13:37.430 --> 00:13:38.580
Nishinoya.

220
00:13:42.420 --> 00:13:44.130
You can do it.

221
00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:45.700
Actually, I can't guarantee that.

222
00:13:46.360 --> 00:13:50.140
That serve is so intense that even 
you're having trouble getting it.

223
00:13:50.140 --> 00:13:54.020
That's Miya Atsumu's serve, 
and that's how it is.

224
00:13:54.850 --> 00:13:58.180
Also, I suck at cheering people up.

225
00:13:58.180 --> 00:14:00.430
I have my hands full dealing with myself.

226
00:14:00.430 --> 00:14:01.770
Really?

227
00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:05.240
But I can also speak for myself.

228
00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:07.200
Even if we can't pull off an A-pass,

229
00:14:07.860 --> 00:14:09.530
I'll make it over!

230
00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:20.960
Yeah, I don't really care 
about the A-pass either,

231
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:22.210
but could you bump the ball higher?

232
00:14:23.120 --> 00:14:24.490
Really?

233
00:14:25.920 --> 00:14:29.270
You know... we really need 
to talk about your timing.

234
00:14:29.270 --> 00:14:30.890
Huh? What's your problem?

235
00:14:30.890 --> 00:14:32.680
Well said, Asahi!

236
00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:34.890
I wanted to say something, too!

237
00:14:34.890 --> 00:14:37.980
Hyogo
Inarizaki

238
00:14:36.200 --> 00:14:37.980
Atsumu...

239
00:14:37.980 --> 00:14:40.910
Seeing Karasuno's setter serve earlier

240
00:14:40.910 --> 00:14:42.690
has made you want to do a 
spike serve, hasn't it?

241
00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:47.780
"Man, it's so much cooler just 
blasting a spike serve."

242
00:14:47.780 --> 00:14:49.580
"I'm getting pretty sick 
of jump floaters, too."

243
00:14:50.130 --> 00:14:51.910
How does he know that?

244
00:14:52.530 --> 00:14:54.780
Your jump floaters are
 scoring right now.

245
00:14:55.460 --> 00:14:58.620
You've been trying to crush their libero,
 so see it all the way through.

246
00:14:58.940 --> 00:14:59.980
Got it!

247
00:15:00.830 --> 00:15:04.540
Inarizaki                                                                                              Karasuno

248
00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.540
The ultimate challengers, Inarizaki.

249
00:15:04.960 --> 00:15:06.670
All right, let's go!

250
00:15:06.670 --> 00:15:07.880
Yeah!

251
00:15:09.140 --> 00:15:11.050
The unknown veterans, Karasuno.

252
00:15:11.050 --> 00:15:13.350
Which team will reach the summit first?

253
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:18.070
The fateful third set starts 
off with Miya Atsumu's serve.

254
00:15:24.980 --> 00:15:27.400
We Don't Need the Memories

255
00:15:37.230 --> 00:15:38.280
Out!

256
00:15:42.010 --> 00:15:44.620
Yeah!

257
00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:47.260
Just how many is he going to get today?! 
The big time server, Miya Atsumu!

258
00:15:46.090 --> 00:15:49.090
We Don't Need the Memories

259
00:15:47.260 --> 00:15:50.480
He's starting off the 
set with a service ace!

260
00:15:49.090 --> 00:15:52.630
Inarizaki                                                                           Karasuno

261
00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:53.690
I totally thought it was out, too.

262
00:15:53.690 --> 00:15:55.880
Atsumu's pretty sharp today.

263
00:15:55.880 --> 00:15:58.220
He might actually get a spike serve over.

264
00:15:58.520 --> 00:16:03.080
Yeah. Maybe the chances of him getting 
either one over won't change that much.

265
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.960
But you just told him to do jump floaters.

266
00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:09.320
When Atsumu serves, 
either choice is powerful.

267
00:16:09.810 --> 00:16:15.000
But if he switches over to a spike serve 
and the other team manages to get it,

268
00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:18.600
he'll end up thinking that he should've 
gone with the jump float serve.

269
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:23.100
But if they got a jump 
floater that looked good,

270
00:16:23.100 --> 00:16:27.790
knowing Atsumu's personality, he'd feel
 even more competitive and motivated.

271
00:16:28.420 --> 00:16:34.220
I think it's better for Atsumu's motivation 
if he gets those jump floaters over.

272
00:16:34.930 --> 00:16:37.850
The scary part is, he's always 
right about this stuff.

273
00:16:51.120 --> 00:16:53.190
My feet feel like they're 
nailed to the floor.

274
00:16:53.590 --> 00:16:56.570
I can tell that my response 
is slower than usual.

275
00:16:57.270 --> 00:16:58.640
I see...

276
00:16:58.640 --> 00:17:01.790
I'm actually scared right now.

277
00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:03.410
Left!

278
00:17:03.410 --> 00:17:04.830
Azumane-san!

279
00:17:07.180 --> 00:17:08.000
Yes!

280
00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:09.760
Nice kill!

281
00:17:09.760 --> 00:17:12.090
Wow, Asahi's actually 
being super dependable.

282
00:17:13.080 --> 00:17:16.970
It's all right for Nishinoya to have 
his hands full every once in a while.

283
00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:22.650
Nice, nice, Asahi! Push it, 
push it, Asahi! One more time!

284
00:17:18.080 --> 00:17:21.390
Karasuno switched up their rotation.

285
00:17:22.650 --> 00:17:25.980
Suguru-kun, feel free to share 
your expert commentary.

286
00:17:26.280 --> 00:17:29.190
Huh? Oh, uh...

287
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:41.370
Serve

288
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:41.370
Back Row

289
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:41.370
Front Row

290
00:17:29.610 --> 00:17:35.370
If there's one unique rule about volleyball, 
I'd say it's the player rotation.

291
00:17:35.370 --> 00:17:38.190
That's where, whenever someone serves,

292
00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:41.370
everyone rotates one position clockwise.

293
00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:43.620
Order Sheet

294
00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:43.870
3rd Set

295
00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:44.750
Karasuno High School

296
00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:45.120
Team Name:

297
00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:45.870
As for the order, they decide that 
before each set starts and submit it.

298
00:17:45.870 --> 00:17:51.250
Front Row

299
00:17:45.870 --> 00:18:00.010
Serve

300
00:17:45.870 --> 00:18:00.010
Setter

301
00:17:45.870 --> 00:18:04.140
Back Row

302
00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:51.070
For example, a common rotation is for the 
setter to start off in the back row.

303
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:55.530
Because that means there'll be three 
attackers up front right off the bat.

304
00:17:51.750 --> 00:17:52.250
Front Row

305
00:17:52.750 --> 00:17:53.250
Front Row

306
00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:54.260
Front Row

307
00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:55.260
Front Row

308
00:17:55.530 --> 00:17:59.580
Also, it's pretty common to start 
off with the strongest server.

309
00:17:55.760 --> 00:18:04.140
Front Row

310
00:17:59.580 --> 00:18:02.240
For Inarizaki, their setter is 
also their most powerful server,

311
00:18:00.510 --> 00:18:01.010
Serve

312
00:18:00.510 --> 00:18:01.010
Setter

313
00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:02.010
Serve

314
00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:02.010
Setter

315
00:18:02.240 --> 00:18:04.140
so both of these rotations apply.

316
00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:03.010
Serve

317
00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:03.010
Setter

318
00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:04.020
Serve

319
00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:04.020
Setter

320
00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:08.040
This is probably the rotation that 
Inarizaki always starts with,

321
00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:09.950
and it's like they're trying to say,

322
00:18:09.950 --> 00:18:12.980
"We don't care what the enemy team looks like!
 This is our starting rotation!"

323
00:18:13.420 --> 00:18:16.650
On the other hand, 
Karasuno tends to dive in headfirst,

324
00:18:16.650 --> 00:18:19.910
but I think they use a lot of trial and error.

325
00:18:20.400 --> 00:18:23.790
Inarizaki seems pretty strong 
regardless of the rotation they use,

326
00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:27.550
but whenever their #4, 
#10, and #11 are up front,

327
00:18:27.550 --> 00:18:29.500
their attack points are at their highest.

328
00:18:29.920 --> 00:18:33.130
But Karasuno is a bit more extreme.

329
00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:35.130
Especially their middle blocker.

330
00:18:35.130 --> 00:18:37.050
Their shrimpy #10 specializes in attacking.

331
00:18:37.050 --> 00:18:40.970
He's basically a scoring machine, and he
 can do it from anywhere on the court.

332
00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:43.350
Also, he's an effective decoy.

333
00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:47.310
Their four-eyes #11 seems to be the 
keystone of their blocking,

334
00:18:47.310 --> 00:18:50.650
so you'd want him to be up there 
when there are strong attackers.

335
00:18:50.650 --> 00:18:55.630
Or maybe they should concentrate everything 
on shutting down Miya Atsumu's serves.

336
00:18:55.630 --> 00:18:59.440
No, no... But starting off with their 
strongest server is vital, too.

337
00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:02.160
Do they go with the setter 
or the samurai dude?

338
00:19:03.660 --> 00:19:05.400
Yeah!

339
00:19:05.400 --> 00:19:07.450
Crap! No one likes a blabbering know-it-all!

340
00:19:07.450 --> 00:19:09.580
Sorry! I talked for way too long!

341
00:19:09.580 --> 00:19:16.090
2nd Set

342
00:19:09.580 --> 00:19:22.430
Net

343
00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:12.880
So the fact that Inarizaki is 
starting with the same rotation,

344
00:19:12.880 --> 00:19:15.460
but Karasuno is switching things up...

345
00:19:16.020 --> 00:19:18.640
Does that mean that when 
Inarizaki tries to score,

346
00:19:16.090 --> 00:19:22.430
3rd Set

347
00:19:18.640 --> 00:19:22.430
Karasuno will have different blockers?

348
00:19:22.430 --> 00:19:24.300
Yes, exactly!

349
00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.650
The match-ups are different!

350
00:19:26.650 --> 00:19:27.690
Every time the rotations change,

351
00:19:27.690 --> 00:19:30.890
we're going to see different 
little battles play out!

352
00:19:30.890 --> 00:19:31.500
Aran!

353
00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:32.560
Got it!

354
00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:35.270
Karasuno manages to get the ace 
Ojiro to touch the ball first!

355
00:19:37.700 --> 00:19:38.690
That's a super-fast quick!

356
00:19:40.490 --> 00:19:41.400
One touch!

357
00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:43.030
Yes!

358
00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:45.870
Why are you freaked out, Hinata?

359
00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:49.750
This is why Karasuno 
chose this rotation.

360
00:19:49.750 --> 00:19:54.250
Net

361
00:19:49.750 --> 00:19:54.250
Now, four-eyes and the 
twins' quick will keep matching up!

362
00:19:55.000 --> 00:19:57.170
All right, let's switch up our rotation.

363
00:19:57.520 --> 00:20:01.550
Even if we don't have Nishinoya in 
the middle of Miya Atsumu's serves,

364
00:20:01.550 --> 00:20:03.940
he's apparently going 
to keep aiming for you.

365
00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:05.140
Talk about stubborn.

366
00:20:05.480 --> 00:20:08.320
Tsukishima, I'm going to have you match up

367
00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:11.100
with Miya Osamu and Suna Rintaro
 as much as possible.

368
00:20:11.450 --> 00:20:13.280
The twins' quick?

369
00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:16.690
Yeah. That's the most unexpected 
thing we've dealt with so far.

370
00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:19.790
I'm counting on you, weirdo quick killer.

371
00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:21.650
Uh... sure.

372
00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:25.110
Hinata's Inuoka strategy was pretty good,

373
00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:28.830
but unfortunately, I'm pretty sure Tanaka's 
getting tired of having to try to block

374
00:20:28.830 --> 00:20:30.790
in the middle for Hinata over and over.

375
00:20:31.750 --> 00:20:35.210
I'd like to say I'm fine, 
but the middle's pretty rough.

376
00:20:36.210 --> 00:20:40.670
You jealous that I got offered 
a big role, Tsukishima-kun?

377
00:20:41.440 --> 00:20:44.840
My bad. I guess I stole 
your big role from you.

378
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:51.880
Tsukishima never forgets 
payback, and he slays.

379
00:20:51.880 --> 00:20:53.810
It's an art form, really.

380
00:20:58.230 --> 00:20:58.980
Samu!

381
00:21:06.280 --> 00:21:06.910
Aran!

382
00:21:08.500 --> 00:21:11.780
The one we don't want on a 
roll the most is Ojiro Aran.

383
00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:17.210
I want him to hit another 
high wall one more time.

384
00:21:28.970 --> 00:21:29.720
Yes!

385
00:21:29.720 --> 00:21:31.660
And he's shut down!

386
00:21:31.660 --> 00:21:33.640
First-year Kageyama Tobio

387
00:21:33.640 --> 00:21:35.100
Fly

388
00:21:33.640 --> 00:21:36.600
stopped the ace Ojiro Aran all on his own!

389
00:21:33.640 --> 00:21:39.380
Good, good, Tobio! Push it, push it,
 Tobio! One more time!

390
00:21:35.100 --> 00:21:36.600
Yes, yes, yes!

391
00:21:37.650 --> 00:21:39.760
They've learned from the second set!

392
00:21:39.760 --> 00:21:43.530
That seems like what Karasuno's 
break point is getting across.

393
00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:43.530
Inarizaki                                                          Karasuno

394
00:21:47.380 --> 00:21:50.280
Nationals always has some amazing blockers.

395
00:21:50.850 --> 00:21:53.790
I can't even count how many 
times I've been shut down.

396
00:21:53.790 --> 00:21:57.520
They come after me as though I look 
completely frozen in time to them,

397
00:21:57.520 --> 00:22:01.270
and there are times they're in front 
of me before I even try to attack.

398
00:22:01.270 --> 00:22:06.150
Those looming hands are 
basically fear itself.

399
00:22:06.150 --> 00:22:07.510
And...

400
00:22:09.280 --> 00:22:12.390
A block that's not scary 
isn't actually a block.

401
00:22:13.380 --> 00:22:17.600
This guy's way scarier than 
four-eyes over there.

402
00:23:51.990 --> 00:23:56.990
Episode 21: Hero

403
00:23:53.280 --> 00:23:55.450
Next time, "Hero."
